{
  "stem": "22979.3",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I'm so confused and so excited about it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "When we-- the first-- end of August, when we came to Birkenau, people who were already sick-- and were sitting there, and couldn't walk the five kilometers-- they were taken by truck.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And they told them they were taken by truck, because, you know, they can't walk.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Those were the first girls who were gassed-- in August 1942.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But in August 1942, I think so-- in Birkenau, the first two crematoriums, one and two, were already finished.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "By the way, you know, Fred was one of the builders of the crematorium.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And so those girls were the first of-- of the gassing, I mean, who already were there six months.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Fred is my husband who was three years also in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But naturally, you know, men and women were not-- in-- in-- in the concentration camps-- separated and in different sections.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I had that will to live, because I always felt the world didn't care about us.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Because I couldn't imagine that people coming from all sides of Europe, that they didn't know where we ended up.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I thought-- I was sure.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But they even told us, they says, that the only way to freedom for us is through the crematorium-- through the chimney.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we knew that survival there is impossible.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I always said, I wait for tomorrow.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Why should I go today?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Maybe-- maybe something will change.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And some by miracle, we will get out of this hell.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So I went day by day.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I said, I never will give up.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Although, I tell you, I was so sick.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I had malaria.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I had dysentery.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But in Auschwitz, to survive, you have also to have close friends who take care of each other.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
